  "text": "The lack of conspecific avoidance could be interpreted as a cognitive deficit, such that ZnT3 KO mice successfully learn to avoid CD-1 mice but fail to generalize the avoidance response to mice of a different strain. This interpretation fits with previous findings of mild impairments in ZnT3 KO mice, including in fear memory [CITATION_1] , texture discrimination (Wu & Dyck, 2018), object recognition memory [CITATION_2] and spatial reversal or working memory (Cole et al., 2011; [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] .",
